computeRefTodos emits todos for the ref graph: TodoRefAdded and TodoRefRemoved for edges appearing in only one of {baseline refs, scan refs}; TodoBrokenRef for refs whose target ID does not resolve to a spec; TodoRefChain for specs transitively reachable (via the undirected ref graph) from a hash-drifted spec, where no covering ref resolution exists at the current source hash; TodoCascade for markers linked to a ref-chain-drifted spec. Propagation is rhizomatic — direction of declared ref edges does not constrain drift propagation. Marker hash-drift does NOT propagate (source-of-truth asymmetry). Cycle-safe via visited-set tracking.